---
target: core
version: 1
validations:
  - name: core-module-exists
    type: folder_check
    path: src/core

  - name: core-types-defined
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the core module defines all required types with correct fields:
      1. Intent - Name, Version, DependsOn, Tags, Profile, Content, FilePath
      2. Validation - Name, Type, Hidden, Parameters
      3. ValidationType - enum with values: file_check, folder_check, command_check, llm_judge
      4. ValidationFile - Target, Version, JudgeProfile, Validations, FilePath
      5. Target - Name, Intent, Validations, Dependencies, Status
      6. TargetStatus - enum with values: pending, building, built, failed, outdated
      7. BuildResult - Target, GenerationID, Success, Error, GeneratedAt, Files, OutputDir
      8. ValidationResult - ValidationName, Passed, Message, Details, Severity
      9. AgentProfile - Name, Provider, Command, CLIArgs, Timeout, Retries, RateLimit, PromptTemplates, Tools, Skills, ModelID
      10. PromptTemplates - Build, Validate, System
      11. ToolConfig - Name, Enabled, Config
      12. SchemaViolation - FilePath, Field, Message, Severity
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/core/**"]

  - name: core-no-internal-imports
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the core module has zero dependencies on other intentc modules.
      It should only import from the standard library and declared third-party dependencies.
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/core/**"]

  - name: core-serialization
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify all core types are serializable to both JSON and YAML.
      Error fields in serializable types must be strings, not error/exception objects.
      AgentProfile must be fully serializable to YAML for config storage.
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/core/**"]

  - name: core-tests-pass
    type: command_check
    command: cd src && uv run pytest core/ -v
    exit_code: 0
---

# Core Types Validations

These validations ensure the core types module is complete, self-contained, and follows the specification. The core module is the foundation - if it's wrong, everything else breaks. The AgentProfile, PromptTemplates, ToolConfig, and SchemaViolation types are essential for the agent profile system and schema validation features.
